tip.text: The smashed avocado toast is perfect for those who like an up sized serving of avocados for their breakfast. Great atmosphere and service.
One of the best ribs in town. The meat is succulent with excellent glaze and flavour in the meat. Comes with a side of potato fries, sweet potato fries and mashed potatoes.
Just a clean and simple hotel that has your bare necessities covered. For those in a ground floor room; there's an added outdoor shower facility in your room.

formattedAddress: Jalan Raya Pengosekan, Ubud Bali (Fish Pond Restaurant Ubud)

tip.text: The signature bebek bengil (crispy duck) is the star dish for this restaurant. Service is excellent along with the atmosphere. Grab a table early at one of the stand-alone huts.
A conveniently located hotel that is service-orientated with the necessary amenities. The rooms all have bolsters for each bed.
Great coffee, food and atmosphere! Their sourdough bread is locally sourced through another local bakery and has a great crunch to each bite.
Nice cozy place for an afternoon drink. I personally prefer the food and drinks at Potato Head Beach Club but the service and atmosphere here makes up for it.
Part of the restaurant is overlooking the lotus pond (hence the name). The food options for lunch is mediocre.
